==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heemraad
<hw>Heem"raad`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu>pl.
<plw>-raaden</plw> <pr>(#)</pr></plu>. <altsp>[Sometimes, incorrectly,
<asp>Heemraat</asp> or even <asp>Heemrad</asp>.]</altsp> <ety>[D.
<ets>heem</ets> village + <ets>raad</ets> council, councilor.]</ety>
<def>In Holland, and, until the 19th century, also in Cape Colony, a
council to assist a local magistrate in the government of rural
districts; hence, also, a member of such a council.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heep</ent>⟦br⟧
